'''[[lithium]] [[fluoride]]'''  (molecular formula ''[[Li]][[F]]'')
#{{chemistry}} a [[salt]] that may be prepared by the action of [[hydrofluoric acid]] on many lithium compounds, and occurs naturally as [[griceite]]; its [[crystal]]s are used in [[optical]] [[instrument]]s, and in [[radiation]] [[dosimetry]] (based on its [[radiothermoluminescence]])